A `select` statement lets a goroutine wait on multiple channel operations.

```go
select {
case v := <-ch1:
    fmt.Println(v)
case ch2 <- val:
    // sent
default:
    // no channel is ready
}
```

Multi-way branch. No fallthrough by default in Go.

```go
switch v {
case 1:
    // ...
case 2:
    // ...
default:
    // ...
}
```

